node.text:
A lone bull elephant stands his ground in the heart of the Maasai Mara, his towering presence both commanding and timeless.  Elephants like this one have roamed Africa for generations, shaping the land with their presence. He looks straight into my lens—into us, into our very soul—reminding us who truly owns the wild. 

This image was taken on our Best of Africa Photo Tour I just finished co-leading with @artofseeingphotography. I’ll be leading this immersive photography trip again next year, as we visit iconic parks in Kenya and Tanzania…who wants to come?

Have you downloaded my FREE Ebook guide on how to Create Impactful Wildlife Images yet?  Hit the link in bio and it’s yours, absolutely free!

www.randallballphotography.com

@rballphoto Thank you for the information. This is Individual 217, a bull in our ElephantBook database. We first sighted him in 2021 grazing alone at Olkinyei Conservancy but later in 2022 we sighted him 3 times alongside three other bulls who also recorded in our database. ^DN
@maraelephantproject Thank you for the ID, pretty impressive guy for the Mara!
